Certainly! Here's an example of how to create an automatically generated table of contents in a LaTeX document using the `titlesec`, `tocloft`, and `hyperref` packages. This example includes section headings, subsections, and a subsubsection.

```latex
\documentclass{article}

% Load required packages
\usepackage{titlesec}
\usepackage{tocloft}
\usepackage{hyperref}

% Customize the table of contents appearance
\setlength{\cftbeforetoctitleskip}{1.5em} % Adjust spacing before the ToC title
\setlength{\cftaftertoctitleskip}{1.5em} % Adjust spacing after the ToC title
\renewcommand{\cftsecleader}{\cftdotfill{\cftdotsep}} % Add a dot leader for sections
\renewcommand{\cftsubsecleader}{\cftdotfill{\cftdotsep}} % Add a dot leader for subsections
\renewcommand{\cftsubsubsecfont}{\bfseries} % Bold font for subsubsections in ToC

% Define the table of contents
\titlecontents{section}
  [1.5em] % Indentation for sections
  {\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{#2}\normalfont\bfseries\large} % Format for the ToC entry
  {}{ #2} % No number for the ToC entry
  {\titlerule*[1.05pt]{.\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;}\contentspage} % Page number

\titlecontents{subsection}
  [3.5em] % Indentation for subsections
  {\addcontentsline{toc}{subsection}{#2}\normalfont\bfseries} % Format for the ToC entry
  {1.5em} % Numbered indentation for the ToC entry
  { #2} % No number for the ToC entry
  {\quad\titlerule*[0.8pt]{.\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;}\contentspage} % Page number

\titlecontents{subsubsection}
  [6.5em] % Indentation for subsubsections
  {\addcontentsline{toc}{subsubsection}{#2}\normalfont\bfseries} % Format for the ToC entry
  {3.5em} % Numbered indentation for the ToC entry
  { #2} % No number for the ToC entry
  {\qquad\titlerule*[0.6pt]{.\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;\;}\contentspage} % Page number

% Document begins here
\begin{document}

% Table of contents
\tableofcontents* % Generate the ToC without numbering it
\thispagestyle{empty} % Remove page number on the ToC page

\section{Example Section}

\subsection{Subsection One}

\subsubsection{Subsubsection One}
Some content goes here for Subsubsection One.

\subsubsection{Subsubsection Two}
Some content goes here for Subsubsection Two.

\subsection{Subsection Two}

\end{document}
```

This example generates an automatically formatted table of contents with customized spacing and leaders for sections, subsections, and subsubsections. The `\tableofcontents*` command generates the table of contents without numbering it, and `\thispagestyle{empty}` removes the page number on the table of contents page. Don't forget to include the necessary packages and customizations at the beginning of your LaTeX document.

